					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">From what I heard, you have to adjust the amount of samples to better match 60hz. You have to do some kind of scaling or buffering, I'm not sure though. All I remember is that the NES runs slightly faster than 60hz so if you generate the proper amount of audio samples, you have more samples that will be played back in the amount of time when using 60hz vsync. So depending on how you generate audio will determine what you can do to fix it. It's also possible to sync to your sound buffer/sound playing I believe. But it can be a tricky problem. The easy way out is to change how many audio samples are generated so you don't have that issue.</div>

